^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Lots to discuss on this hand. First, let me start with the bidding.  dee does not really have an opening hand, as it does not meet the rule of 20.  4-3-3-3 hands with 12 HCP and no aces are not really good opening bids.  But assuming dee opens, elizabeth has 2 choices of bids.  She can either bid 1@H as she did. Another alternative is the unusual 2N, showing 5/5 in the 2 lower unbid suits (hearts and diamonds in this case.)  I think I personally would have chosen 2N, but 1@H is certainly acceptable.  1@S is the correct bid by josie.|
