because you can correct 5@C to 5@D, and partner will realize you had hearts and diamonds rather than diamonds and clubs. Some people play that 4N over a 4@s preempt shows any 2 suiter (clubs/diamonds, diamonds/hearts, or clubs/hearts). If you play that, responder should only bid 5@D if he can tolerate playing in hearts (in case responder has the club/heart hand).|
